problem.markdown:
>>Which of the following statements about the modular approach is true?<<

(x) A module implements some data transformation and is required to perform automatic differentiation.
( ) To create a module, we must implement the following three functions: forward, backward and update. The implementation of backward and update can be handled by automatic differentiation. 
( ) An activation function is not a module because it doesn’t have parameters. {{An activation function must propagate gradients from its outputs to its inputs. In this case, the implementation of the update function is empty.}}
( ) A loss function is not a module since it is used to evaluate a model and so, it cannot be part of the model.  {{There is a subtle difference between a model that gives a prediction and the whole computational graph that supports automatic differentiation.}}

||Refer to the videos in section 3.1.2 about the modular approach.||
